All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
ActiveActor
The ActiveActor class is an abstract class that represents an active actor in the game.
ActiveActorDestructible
The ActiveActorDestructible class is an abstract class that represents an active actor in the game which can be destroyed.
ActorManager
The ActorManager class manages the actors in the game, including friendly units, enemy units, and projectiles.
BackgroundManager
The BackgroundManager class manages the background image for the game.
BossPlane
Represents a boss plane in the game, which has a shield and follows a specific movement pattern.
BossProjectile
Represents a projectile fired by the boss plane in the game.
CollisionManager
The CollisionManager class handles collisions between actors in the game.
Destructible
The Destructible interface defines the methods required for an object to be destructible.
EnemyManager
The EnemyManager class manages the enemy units in the game.
EnemyPlane
Represents an enemy plane in the game, which moves horizontally and can fire projectiles.
EnemyPlane2
Represents a second type of enemy plane in the game, which moves horizontally and can fire projectiles.
EnemyProjectile
Represents a projectile fired by an enemy plane in the game.
FighterPlane
Represents a fighter plane in the game, which can move and fire projectiles.
GameController
The GameController class manages the game's flow, including launching the game, transitioning between levels, and handling errors.
GameLauncher
The GameLauncher class is the entry point for the game application.
GameOverImage
The GameOverImage class is a custom ImageView that displays a "Game Over" image.
GameStateManager
The GameStateManager class manages the game state, including win and lose conditions.
HeartDisplay
The HeartDisplay class manages a display of heart images within a JavaFX HBox.
HorizontalMovementStrategy
The HorizontalMovementStrategy class implements the MovementStrategy interface.
HorizontalProjectileMovementStrategy
The HorizontalProjectileMovementStrategy class implements the ProjectileMovementStrategy interface.
InputManager
The InputManager class manages user input for controlling the user plane and firing projectiles.
InputManager.ProjectileFiredListener
Interface for listening to projectile firing events.
LeaderboardScreen
The LeaderboardScreen class displays the leaderboard with the times of each playthrough.
LevelBoss
The LevelBoss class represents the boss level in the game.
LevelBossView
The LevelBossView class represents the visual components of the boss level, including the display and management of the shield image.
LevelFactory
The LevelFactory class is responsible for creating instances of different game levels.
LevelOne
The LevelOne class represents the first level in the game.
LevelParent
The Level Parent is an abstract class that represent a level in the game.
LevelTransitionScreen
The LevelTransitionScreen class manages the transition screen between levels, including animations and text display.
LevelTwo
The LevelTwo class represents the second level in the game.
LevelView
The LevelView class represents the visual components of a game level, including the display of hearts for player health and a game over image.
LevelViewFactory
The LevelViewFactory class is responsible for creating instances of different level views.
MainMenu
The MainMenu class creates the main menu interface for the game, including buttons to start the game, view instructions, and exit.
MovementStrategy
The MovementStrategy interface defines the method required for a movement strategy.
MusicController
The MusicController class manages the playback of background music in the game.
PauseManager
The PauseManager class manages the pause functionality in the game.
PauseScreen
The PauseScreen class represents a pause screen in a JavaFX application.
PlaneFactory
The PlaneFactory class is responsible for creating instances of different types of planes.
Projectile
Represents a projectile in the game, which can move and take damage.
ProjectileFactory
The ProjectileFactory class is responsible for creating instances of different types of projectiles.
ProjectileFiringStrategy
The ProjectileFiringStrategy interface defines the method required for a projectile firing strategy.
ProjectileManager
The ProjectileManager class manages the projectiles fired by both user and enemy units in the game.
ProjectileMovementStrategy
The ProjectileMovementStrategy interface defines the method required for a projectile movement strategy.
ProjectileSoundController
The ProjectileSoundController class manages the playback of sound effects for projectiles.
ShieldActivation
The ShieldActivation class manages the activation and deactivation of a shield for an actor.
ShieldImage
The ShieldImage class extends ImageView to display a shield image at a specified position and size within a JavaFX application.
StatusTextManager
The StatusTextManager class manages the status text displayed on the screen.
TimelineManager
The TimelineManager class manages the game loop timeline for updating the scene.
TimerManager
The TimerManager class manages the timing for different levels in the game.
UserPlane
Represents the user's plane in the game, which can move in all directions and fire projectiles.
UserProjectile
Represents a projectile fired by the user's plane in the game.
VerticalMovementStrategy
The VerticalMovementStrategy class implements the MovementStrategy interface.
WinGameScreen
The WinGameScreen class displays the screen shown when the player wins the game.
